Package udel.GardenProject.windows

All the distinct windows that can be displayed to the user. All classes in this package extend from the abstract class Window.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Team 0
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllPlants
    A searchable database of all the plants a user can add to the their plot.
    BluePrint
    Allow the user detail the background of their plot with labels, and specify characteristics for some areas of their plot.
    Download
    Where the user can export their plot as a PNG/JPEG, save it as a .gardenproject file, load a saved project, or exit.
    ExistingPlants
    Where a user can specify what plants already exist in their garden.
    PlantInfo
    To display all the information of a Plant to the user.
    PlantSelection
    To display all the information of a Plant to the user.
    PlotDesign
    Heart of the application: Where the user can drag plants, obstacles, shade, text boxes, and interact with their virtual, top-down plot.
    PreviousSaves
    Displays a short table of where a user has recently saved Sessions on their disk.
    Questionnaire
    Basic questions about a user's plots that informs what plants are selected.
    SeasonView
    Preview the garden as it will appear in every season and 1, 2, and 3 years down the line.
    Tutorial
    Presently: Basic text description run down of all the features of the program and how to use them.
    Welcome
    Welcome screen that first appears when the user starts the program.
    Window
    A window that can be displayed to the user.
